<html lang="en">
    <%- include('./partials/header.ejs') %>
<body>
    <!-- Top Nav Bar -->
    <%- include('./partials/navbar.ejs') %>

      <!-- Header -->
      

    <!-- Main Content Section -->
    <main id="learn-about-blood">
        
        <!-- Introduction to Blood -->
        <section class="content-section">
            <h2>Introduction to Blood</h2>
            <p>Blood is a vital fluid that circulates through the human body, transporting oxygen, nutrients, and waste products. It plays a crucial role in maintaining life and health.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- Components of Blood -->
        <section class="content-section">
            <h2>Components of Blood</h2>
            <div class="content-container">
                <img src="./images/types of cells.jpg" alt="Components of Blood" class="related-image">
                <div class="text-content">
                    <h3>Red Blood Cells (RBCs)</h3>
                    <p>Red blood cells carry oxygen from the lungs to the rest of the body.</p>

                    <h3>White Blood Cells (WBCs)</h3>
                    <p>White blood cells are part of the immune system and help fight infections.</p>

                    <h3>Platelets</h3>
                    <p>Platelets help in blood clotting and wound healing.</p>

                    <h3>Plasma</h3>
                    <p>Plasma is the liquid part of blood, containing proteins, nutrients, and hormones.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Blood Types -->
        <section class="content-section">
            <h2>Blood Types</h2>
            <div class="content-container">
                <img src="./images/bookimg.jpg" alt="Blood Types" class="related-image">
                <div class="text-content">
                    <p>Blood is classified into different types based on the presence or absence of certain antigens. The main blood types are A, B, AB, and O, each of which can be positive or negative.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- The Role of Blood in the Body -->
        <section class="content-section">
            <h2>The Role of Blood in the Body</h2>
            <p>Blood circulates throughout the body, delivering oxygen and nutrients to cells, removing waste products, and regulating body temperature and pH levels.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- The Blood Donation Process -->
        <section class="content-section">
            <h2>The Blood Donation Process</h2>
            <div class="content-container">
                <img src="./images/proceessblood.jpg" alt="Blood Donation Process" class="related-image">
                <div class="text-content">
                    <p>Donating blood is a safe and simple process. Learn about the steps involved in donating blood and how it can save lives.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Benefits of Blood Donation -->
        <section class="content-section">
            <h2>Benefits of Blood Donation</h2>
            <p>Donating blood not only saves lives but also provides health benefits to the donor, such as health checks and a sense of community contribution.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- Related Blood Conditions -->
        <section class="content-section">
            <h2>Related Blood Conditions</h2>
            <div class="content-container">
                <img src="./images/benefitsssssssssssss.jpg" alt="Blood Conditions" class="related-image">
                <div class="text-content">
                    <p>Learn about common blood-related conditions, such as anemia, hemophilia, and sickle cell disease, and how they affect the body.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

    </main>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <%- include('./partials/footer.ejs') %>     
</body>
</html>